These specimens represent the first North American report of this apparently Palearctic species (
Figures 1­5
). It is widely distributed throughout Europe, east throughout eastern and western Siberia, and south to the North African coast ( Löbl and Smetana, 2004 ). In Europe it is known to inhabit the nests of mammals and birds ( Bickhardt 1907 , Heinemann 1910 , Strand 1967 ).
